# read me


Compile java code using makefile, use make command. Tested in the school environment on hosts ubuntu1604-006 and ubuntu1604-008 using the school versions of compilers and other tools.


EXECUTION:
On hostX run the nse emulator with command: nse <hostY> <nse_port>

After running emulator, on hostY run the 5 routers: java router <routerNum> <hostX> <nse_port> <router_port>


As per assignment specifications, script "router" runs my java program as a background processes. 

Usage: ./router <router_number> <hostX> <nse_port> <router_port>


EXAMPLE EXECUTION:
On hostX run:  ./nselinux386 ubuntu1604-008 8945

On hostY run:  ./router 1 localhost 8945 8944
               ./router 2 localhost 8945 8943
               ./router 3 localhost 8945 8942
               ./router 4 localhost 8945 8941
               ./router 5 localhost 8945 8940